    <intro>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span size="3"&gt;&lt;span face="Calibri"&gt;Be sure to read the &lt;span&gt;&lt;a title="opens in this window - Helping Learners Persist" href="http://www.ncsall.net/index.html@id=771&amp;amp;pid=332.html" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;background reading&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;on &lt;i&gt;“Helping Adults Persist.”&lt;/i&gt; Then read the &lt;span&gt;&lt;a title="pdf - opens in new window - Meet Your Students and Help Them Set Realistic Learning Goals" href="@@PLUGINFILE@@/Meet%20Your%20Students%20Scenario.pdf" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Meet Your Students and Help Them Set Realistic Learning Goals&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; scenario, pick three students, and post answers to these questions in the discussion forum:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span size="3"&gt;&lt;span face="Calibri"&gt;What you would do to help each of the three to set realistic learning goals? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span size="3" face="Calibri"&gt;What would you do throughout the semester to ensure that they never lose sight of their goals and that they see the progress they are making toward their goals?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
